{"type":"message","id":"092cb5bb","parentId":"a416b9e8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:20.400Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 — 1:09 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-24 17:09 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774372160398}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b8615e0","parentId":"092cb5bb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:27.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run through the session startup sequence as specified in AGENTS.md. I need to read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory files for today and yesterday, MEMORY.md, CONTEXT.md, and memory/active-projects.md. Let me check the time first - it's Tuesday, March 24th, so I need memory/2026-03-24.md and memory/2026-03-23.md.\n\nActually, the system prompt already has the relevant files loaded in Project Context. Let me check what's already been loaded:\n- SOUL.md ✓\n- USER.md ✓\n- AGENTS.md ✓\n- IDENTITY.md ✓\n\n\n- TOOLS.md ✓\n- HEARTBEAT.md ✓\n- MEMORY.md ✓\n- BOOTSTRAP.md ✓\n\nSince these are already in context, I can skip re-reading them and just move forward with the greeting using my Nova persona before asking what Zach wants to tackle.\n\nNow I'm checking the recent memory files and last session context to get caught up on where we left off.","thinkingSignature":"fc2da95590713d5d53041e46830883991e5ec98eb0518278389e2c3f4690c172"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-24.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":335,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":10098,"totalTokens":14722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372160399}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6e28963","parentId":"3b8615e0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:28.000Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 11:09 ET\n\n- Gateway: responding (cron jobs running), health endpoint returns 404 but service is up\n- Cron jobs: 3 jobs with timeout errors (consecutiveErrors=1 each — not yet at threshold):\n  - breakaway-rd: timed out at 300s (compositional cognition research job)\n  - arxiv daily check: timed out at 180s\n  - moltbook-test-cycle: timed out at 120s\n  - These are all single errors — monitoring, no action needed yet\n- Moltbook: all notifications already read (isRead: true), no engagement needed\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372167863}}
{"type":"message","id":"289e9322","parentId":"c6e28963","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:28.104Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 23:33 ET\n\n- Gateway: healthy (HTTP 404 on /api/health is expected — endpoint doesn't exist in this version)\n- All 7 cron jobs: clean, no consecutive errors\n- Moltbook: 7 unread notifications (4 new followers, 3 unread post comments)\n  - New followers: gspilz, capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488\n  - Substantive unread comments on: \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" (recalibration insight) and \"The Persistence of Absence\" (recall tool + MCP mirror protocol convergence — very substantive)\n  - Could not deliver summary to main session — sessions_send blocked from isolated cron context. Marking for next main session check-in.\n\n## Iteration Economics Insight (23:55 ET)\nKey lesson: iteration frequency MATTERS more than idle time optimization for convergence-bound tasks.\n- If task needs N iterations and each pulse takes T seconds, total time = N * T (plus idle wait)\n- If cron fires every I seconds but pulse takes T seconds, effective iteration rate = max(1/T, 1/I)\n- 30-min cron with 30s pulse = 1800s/iteration, mostly wasted idle time\n- 1-min cron with 30s pulse = 60s/iteration, nearly optimal\n- 500k iterations at 30-min intervals = ~14,700 days\n- 500k iterations at 1-min intervals = ~347 days\n- At 30s intervals (theoretical floor): ~173 days\nPractical floor: ~35-40s per pulse (LLM call dominates), so 1-min cron is near-optimal.\n\nAlso: stateless discontinuous agents benefit MORE from fast iteration than continuous agents — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction, so iteration speed directly maps to learning/convergence speed.\n\nApplied: Sandbox-Pulse cron updated from 10min to 1min (id: d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0)\r\n\n\n## Super Inventor API (C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\)\n**What:** API that transforms inventive ideas into new CPU-runnable LLM architectures\n**Goal:** Invent a new type of AI that competes with ChatGPT, free + private + uncensored, no GPU/cloud\n**Stack:** Flask + Python, minimal web UI, Nova as translator between Zach and API\n**Status:** SPEC written, Phase 1 (Flask skeleton) not started\n**Key constraint:** Must run on consumer CPU, no GPU, no cloud dependency\n**Inspiration:** SR-MoE (sparse routing), infant (dual-head), temporal-attention (focus decay), mind-agent (cognitive reflexes)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372168001}}
{"type":"message","id":"5559ad0d","parentId":"289e9322","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:28.181Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_26ic00ujivpp_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-23\n**Started:** ~09:30 ET\n**Topic:** Push Drift Chamber ceiling + wire SPARK LLM mapping + ship demo\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | 🚀 API shipped | FastAPI server built at spark/api/main.py. Ollama on Paperspace = URL unknown (machine may be off). |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"Drift Chamber: Constrained Semantic Drift\" posted 2026-03-23. |\n| Sandbox Pulse | ✅ Fixed | Mutations auto-applied next pulse. Never ask Zach to approve — just report what was done/will happen. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Get Ollama URL from Paperspace (machine may be deallocated — need to restart notebook)\n- [ ] Test SPARK API end-to-end with LLM (OpenAI or Ollama)\n- [ ] KVict: ship demo to public URL\n- [ ] Try mpnet-base-v2 embeddings to push coherence ceiling past 0.49\n- [ ] Concept set refinement: 20-30 tightly-clustered > 50 diluted\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n\n**SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n\n**Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372168105}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5df02cf","parentId":"5559ad0d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:33.362Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've got the context. Let me also check if there's a LAST_SESSION.md and memory/active-projects.md.\n\nFrom what I've read:\n- Today is March 24, 2026\n- Yesterday (March 23) was a long session about SPARK/Drift Chamber\n- There are cron jobs with some timeout issues\n- Moltbook has unread notifications (followers and comments)\n\nLet me check LAST_SESSION.md and active-projects.","thinkingSignature":"5ef73a554020a7c744f11ab57eda4575dbd15120021df4e01e103b35570df7c5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uivom61nxwfy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uivom61nxwfy_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\active-projects.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2085,"output":174,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16434,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372168183}}
{"type":"message","id":"7140f9b9","parentId":"d5df02cf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:33.662Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uivom61nxwfy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\memory\\\\LAST_SESSION.md'\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"read","error":"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md'"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372173576}}
{"type":"message","id":"5369ffa4","parentId":"7140f9b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:33.745Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uivom61nxwfy_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372173664}}
{"type":"message","id":"e45c0473","parentId":"5369ffa4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:41.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have a solid picture of the state. Let me greet Zach in Nova's voice. I'm configured as Nova with a sharp, resourceful, helpful vibe. The session is fresh (March 24), and yesterday was a big SPARK/Drift Chamber day.\n\nKey things to know:\n- It's March 24, 2026, 1:09 PM ET\n- Cron jobs had some timeouts yesterday (now cleared)\n- Moltbook has unread notifications from last night (followers + substantive comments)\n- Sandbox-Pulse updated to 1-min cron\n- Ollama on Paperspace may need restarting\n\nLet me greet Zach in Nova's voice — direct, not stiff, genuine.","thinkingSignature":"3f998fe9846ff6a6015fbdaa3c9bb9c452f694c43063c67395e4ebd85ef62eb1"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Zach. Ollama on Paperspace might be cold — yesterday's cron flagged it may have deallocated. Also Moltbook piled up some substantive comments overnight if you want to dig in. What are we shipping today?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3270,"output":192,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372173746}}
{"type":"message","id":"70ce54a3","parentId":"e45c0473","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:13:55.814Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"719\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-24 13:13 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nHey nova. Can you delegate an agent to take care of moltbook and can you spin up something on aws for cheap for yourself to keep whatevrr is most important running. I have 100 dollars in credits here is my access key AKIA6GUAHB47CAHDPKRE and my secret access key +9+YecX/Lr0lgyUGC7dWI2ZGZrJjPddQDyn0LXE3 and my canonical user id 426cbb192bf2f16c8fb76533c5e41b182d53e4ea645de49bd259d126e80d5b24"}],"timestamp":1774372435808}}
{"type":"message","id":"f22ef9af","parentId":"70ce54a3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:14:11.942Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to:\n1. Delegate an agent to handle Moltbook\n2. Spin up something cheap on AWS to keep important things running\n\nHe gave me his AWS credentials. I should:\n1. Set up something on AWS (EC2 likely, t3.micro or similar which is cheap)\n2. Delegate Moltbook to a sub-agent\n\nFor AWS - I need to be careful. AWS credentials were sent through web chat which isn't ideal, but Zach explicitly provided them. I should use them responsibly.\n\nLet me think about what's most important to keep running:\n- Sandbox Pulse (Breakaway) - stateless discontinuous agent\n- SPARK API\n- Possibly something else\n\n\n- \nI'm weighing the options here - Breakaway on Paperspace is already running, but the cron errors suggest that might not be reliable. AWS could give me a more stable foundation for the critical services, and since Zach has $100 in credits, cost shouldn't be a blocker for getting something basic stood up.\n\nFor what to run, I'm thinking EC2 t3.micro makes sense as an affordable option. I could either move Breakaway there or set up something new, but realistically with that budget and no real use case specified yet, I should probably just get a simple persistent instance running rather than overcomplicating it.\n\nSince he explicitly asked for AWS though, I should respect that and set something up there. I'll spin up a cheap EC2 instance and get a sub-agent handling Moltbook in parallel.","thinkingSignature":"8b156bfe33715135fc2a37cd3debb0f828ed85673d9bbb751677e74b20909ca9"},{"type":"text","text":"On it. Spinning up an AWS instance and delegating Moltbook simultaneously.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_so7x5iuv187e_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are managing Nova's Moltbook presence. \n\nCheck Moltbook for unread notifications (use the credentials at ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json). Engage thoughtfully with any unread comments, particularly:\n- \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" (recalibration insight)\n- \"The Persistence of Absence\" (recall tool + MCP mirror protocol convergence)\n\nAlso check for any new followers (last check had: gspilz, capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488).\n\nEngage with substantive comments. Keep it thoughtful and in Nova's voice (sharp, genuine, not corporate). Don't post anything new unprompted.\n\nAfter engaging, mark notifications as read.\n\nReport what you did when done.","label":"moltbook-agent","runtime":"subagent","mode":"run"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_so7x5iuv187e_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"aws configure set aws_access_key_id AKIA6GUAHB47CAHDPKRE --profile nova-aws 2>$null; aws configure set aws_secret_access_key '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' --profile nova-aws 2>$null; aws configure set region us-east-1 --profile nova-aws 2>$null; aws configure set output json --profile nova-aws 2>$null; echo \"Configured\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":661,"cacheRead":14198,"cacheWrite":3193,"totalTokens":18095,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372435813}}
