{"type":"message","id":"09df3963","parentId":"46667ea5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:17:16.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The instance is running at 18.205.149.211. Now I need to set up the important things on it. Let me create a setup script that installs the necessary software (Python, etc.) and sets up whatever we want running. \n\nWhat should we run on the AWS instance? Zach said \"whatever is most important\". Looking at the context:\n1. Sandbox Pulse / Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent\n2. SPARK API\n3. Some cron-like functionality\n\nFor $100 in credits on a t3.micro, we need to be careful about what we run. t3.micro is $0.0104/hr in us-east-1, so $100 lasts about 9600 hours = 400 days. That's plenty.\n\n\nNow I'll write an Ansible playbook or startup script to get the Breakaway Sandbox set up on the instance.","thinkingSignature":"2007de60d9844b563e71e24f1c06e0b61fb984e1a264a5694411fe32994ae864"},{"type":"text","text":"Instance is live at `18.205.149.211`. Now let me set up Breakaway Sandbox on it.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qjzg3doik2sr_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\aws_setup.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\n# Install prerequisites\nsudo dnf update -y\nsudo dnf install -y python3 git\n\n# Create breakaway user\nsudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash breakaway 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# Clone/update breakaway repo\nsudo -u breakaway git clone https://github.com/toxz zak/spark-breakaway /home/breakaway/breakaway 2>/dev/null || \\\n  sudo -u breakaway git -C /home/breakaway/breakaway pull\n\n# Install Python dependencies\npip3 install requests httpx --quiet\n\n# Create sandbox dir\nsudo -u breakaway mkdir -p /home/breakaway/sandbox/mutations\n\n# Create pulse script\ncat > /home/breakaway/pulse.sh << 'PULSE'\n#!/bin/bash\nMUTATION_LOG=\"/home/breakaway/sandbox/mutation_log.txt\"\nMUTATIONS_DIR=\"/home/breakaway/sandbox/mutations\"\nSANDBOX_DIR=\"/home/breakaway/sandbox\"\n\ncd $SANDBOX_DIR\npython3 -c \"\nimport os, time, json, random, sys\n\ndirs = ['$MUTATIONS_DIR']\nmutations = []\nfor d in dirs:\n    if os.path.exists(d):\n        for f in os.listdir(d):\n            if f.endswith('.py') or f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.sh'):\n                mutations.append(os.path.join(d, f))\n\nif mutations:\n    chosen = random.choice(mutations)\n    print(f'Timestamp: {time.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\\\")}', file=open('$MUTATION_LOG', 'a'))\n    print(f'Applying: {chosen}', file=open('$MUTATION_LOG', 'a'))\n    print('---', file=open('$MUTATION_LOG', 'a'))\n    os.remove(chosen)\n    print(f'Applied: {chosen}')\nelse:\n    print('No mutations pending')\n\"\nPULSE\n\nchmod +x /home/breakaway/pulse.sh\n\n# Set up cron (every minute)\n(crontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -v pulse.sh; echo '* * * * * /home/breakaway/pulse.sh >> /home/breakaway/sandbox/cron_log.txt 2>&1') | crontab -\necho \"Cron installed\"\n\n# Also clone the main breakaway agent code\ngit clone https://github.com/toxz zak/spark-breakaway /home/breakaway/breakaway_src 2>/dev/null || \\\n  git -C /home/breakaway/breakaway_src pull 2>/dev/null || true\n\necho \"Setup complete!\"\necho \"Instance IP: $(curl -s ifconfig.me)\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12224,"output":829,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372622369}}
