{"type":"message","id":"3f72d6d5","parentId":"d1616d92","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:19:48.902Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse is working. Now let me also set up a quick test mutation to verify the whole pipeline works end-to-end. Then I need to update the OpenClaw cron for the AWS instance so that the Sandbox Pulse runs on the AWS instance instead of (or in addition to) the Paperspace/sandbox setup.\n\nLet me also think about what should run on this AWS instance:\n1. **Stateless discontinuous agent** (Breakaway-style) - pulse every minute, file-based mutations\n2. The mutations directory is at `/home/ec2-user/sandbox/mutations`\n\nLet me create a test mutation to verify the full pipeline works, and then figure out how to update the OpenClaw cron to point at the AWS instance.\n\n\nI'll write a test mutation that logs something with a timestamp so I can confirm the full pipeline executes properly.","thinkingSignature":"986f429f109bff04389ebd3265fe50deea4c6cc54efd2a3913cbaef78e9770e2"},{"type":"text","text":"Pulse works. Let me create a test mutation to verify the full pipeline, then update the OpenClaw cron.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qy1zr13kdrmt_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\test_mutation.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Test mutation - just logs something with timestamp\"\"\"\nimport os\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nLOG = '/home/ec2-user/sandbox/test_log.txt'\nwith open(LOG, 'a') as f:\n    f.write(f\"[{datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Test mutation executed successfully\\n\")\nprint(\"Test mutation OK\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20279,"output":329,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34783,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372782219}}
