{"type":"message","id":"f6bf1ec5","parentId":"fc152cdd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:23:08.633Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to know how many times Breakaway could run for $3, given the model's pricing.\n\nBreakaway uses MiniMax-M2.7. I need to check the pricing for MiniMax-M2.7. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMiniMax-M2.7 pricing - I should check the TOOLS.md or look this up. From memory, MiniMax-M2.7 has a certain cost per 1M tokens or per query. But Breakaway runs as an isolated agentTurn job - let me think about what model it uses.\n\nLooking at the breakaway-rd cron job payload:\n```json\n\n\n{\n  \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n  \"message\": \"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL...\",\n  \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n}\n```\n\nThis doesn't specify a model, so it uses the default. The default model from session_status is `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`.\n\nNow I need to find MiniMax-M2.7's pricing. From what I recall, MiniMax-M2.7 has input and output token costs that I should look up to calculate how many Breakaway runs could fit in $3.\n\nThe Sandbox-Pulse-10min is what's actually running Breakaway frequently - it's configured to run every 60 seconds, not 10 minutes. It invokes an isolated agentTurn with a 120-second timeout using MiniMax-M2.7. At $0.05-0.10 per 1M tokens, even at 30 seconds per run with 100K tokens, that's roughly $0.01 per run, so for $3 I could get around 300 runs.\n\nBut I need to be more careful about this estimate and actually look up the current MiniMax pricing since I don't have the exact numbers memorized.","thinkingSignature":"a97b6816780b7bae5002c8429cd6ba990029fd64bb3ae74b822514e5f30dc4cb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vzm55817t00u_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"MiniMax M2.7 API pricing per 1 million tokens 2025"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":415,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":