{"type":"message","id":"525007b8","parentId":"b96d3f0f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:23:33.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No memory results. Let me think about what I know about MiniMax-M2.7 pricing. Looking at various AI API pricing:- MiniMax-M2.7 is typically in the $0.01-0.05 per 1M tokens range for input, and similar for output\n\nActually, I think MiniMax-M2.7 is quite cheap. Let me think... looking at common MiniMax pricing:\n- Input: ~$0.01-0.03 per 1M tokens\n- Output: ~$0.03-0.10 per 1M tokens\n\nBut I should be honest that I'm not 100% sure of the exact current pricing. \n\nLet me work through a concrete estimate instead of guessing. Each Breakaway run processes a full context window, so if I assume around 50K tokens total per run (input plus output), and MiniMax-M2.7's rate is roughly $0.05 per million tokens combined, that works out to about half a cent per run. So Zach's $3 budget could theoretically support somewhere in the range of hundreds to thousands of runs depending on the actual pricing tiers.\n\nThe real issue is that I don't have the exact MiniMax pricing memorized, and charging $3/hr suggests a very cheap model. Given that MiniMax-M2.7 is their flagship reasoning model, it's probably on the higher end of their pricing spectrum—maybe $2-3 per million tokens. Without the precise numbers, I'm stuck between giving a rough estimate or being honest about the uncertainty.\n\nLet me reconsider the actual use case. Zach is asking how many times Breakaway can run on $3. If each run costs $0.01 (which would be 300 runs for $3), that's probably too expensive for MiniMax. More realistically, at $0.001 per run, he'd get 3000 runs. The honest answer is I don't have the exact pricing, so I should look for it somewhere in the workspace files or just admit I don't know.","thinkingSignature":"77857c4d6bf7a873d41df36bf29284b6be84ea77eb3b1f1d6770c80fca8e25f0"},{"type":"text","text":"Don't have the exact MiniMax-M2.7 pr