{"type":"message","id":"9ff05df1","parentId":"4963ed03","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:24:06.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the pricing. MiniMax-M2.5 has:\n- Input: $0.3 per 1M tokens\n- Output: $1.2 per 1M tokens\n- Cache read: $0.03 per 1M tokens\n- Cache write: $0.12 per 1M tokens\n\nWait, but the runtime says MiniMax-M2.7 not M2.5. Let me check if M2.7 has pricing listed too. The model in use is `MiniMax-M2.7`.\n\nActually, looking at the docs, it only shows M2.5 pricing. But M2.7 is the current runtime model. \n\nFor M2.7, I'm not seeing explicit pricing in the docs, so I'll need to estimate based on the M2.5 rates. Let me work through the actual token consumption for a Breakaway run—it's got a 120-second timeout with the full 200K context window, but the actual tokens used would depend on the prompt size and response length. With a typical prompt around 1000-2000 tokens and responses ranging from 50K to 100K tokens, the math gets tricky fast.\n\nI'm estimating roughly 100K tokens total per run (60K output plus 40K input), which at M2.5's rates comes to about $0.138 per run. That's only around 21 runs for $3, which feels expensive—but the docs mention M2.5 produces more concise responses, so the actual output might be smaller than I'm calculating. Though now I'm realizing the actual model being used is MiniMax-M2.7, not M2.5, which might have different pricing.\n\nLooking at the runtime info, the model is listed as MiniMax-M2.7, which could just be an alias for M2.5 or a newer version with its own pricing. Given the context window is 200K tokens and most runs probably use 20-50K tokens total, I'm estimating roughly $0.01-0.05 per run, which would give me around 60-300 runs for $3. That's still not great, so I should look for M2.7-specific pricing or check the OpenClaw models list to get a clearer picture.","thinkingSignature":"a9fed90b9af7b99aea9becb594501133bc1f2c547c3aa780cf9b01732a8a6e73"},{"type":"text","text":"M2.5 pricing from the docs: **$0.30/1M input, $1.20/1M output**. M2.7 should be similar or slightly more.\n\nRough Breakaway run estimate (120s timeout, ~100K tokens total including context):\n- ~$0.05–0.10 per run\n\n**~$30–60 runs for $3** at that rate. That's not many"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30885,"output":0,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45060,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1774376631413,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted."}}
